<br>
The Golden Idol of Tunare is one of the nine pieces to the EoS quest (Earring of Solstice - FT 1). The idols can sell anywhere from 800pp to 1500pp (on Saryn server). As an enchanter, you could make these for as little as 600pp or lower depending on cost of supplies and success rate.<br>
<br>
First you need to get your skill to 180 minimum - my shammy has a skill of 194 at the moment and I have about a 50-75% success rate. The higher the better. A geerlok is recommended as well. You will need to have a minimum bank balance of 5Kpp. This will allow you to purchase enough for 10-15 attempts.<br>
<br>
As a shammy the most expensive component is the Distilled Mana (350pp) but as an enchanter (lvl 39) the cost would be 212pp - 2 sapphires plus 1 poison vial - using your mass distill mana spell.<br>
<br>
Most ingredients are storebought and I have found that the best place to make them is PoK. You will need to combine in a pottery wheel:-<br>
<br>
Sculpting Tool (returned on success or failure)<br>
Flask of Water<br>
Gold Bar<br>
Idol Sketch<br>
Large Block of Magic Clay (do it yourself - lvl 8 spell - or  <br>
                                    buy it in Bazaar for 4-5pp)<br>
Imbued Emerald (I have a friend who does these for me or<br>
                      buy them in Bazaar for 20-25pp)<br>
Vial of Distilled Mana (2 sapphires   1 poison vial - spell - no <br>
                             fail)<br>
Celestial Essence (made in mortar &amp; pestle - no fail - Scent <br>
                        of Marr &amp; Celestial Solvent - cost 3pp - or <br>
                        buy in Bazaar for approx 5-8pp)<br>
<br>
This will give you an Unfired Golden Idol of Tunare. Combine in a kiln:-<br>
<br>
Unfired Golden Idol of Tunare<br>
High Quality Firing Sheet<br>
Divine Crystalline Glaze<br>
(no fail combine in a glaze mortar - combine Water Flask, <br>
Permafrost Crystals, Iron Oxide and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>White Lead</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->)<br>
<br>
Permafrost Crystals can be found on the goblins in Permafrost Keep. It is an uncommon drop. There are also 7 ground spawns. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>White Lead</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> can be made in a mortar &amp; pestle (no fail) by combining Lead Sulphide &amp; Limestone (both items bought from dwarf merchant in Kaladim near Bank). Iron Oxide costs about 100pp in Bazaar but can be found as low as 50pp - just be patient and look each time you log on. I have a trade mule in Bazaar to look for the items I need. <br>
<br>
Some hints to help you - get KEI if you can otherwise have your int/wis as high as possible. Max your strength &amp; dexterity if you can - find a shammy to cast Infusion of Spirit &amp; dexterity buff. I have found these to be the most beneficial buffs when pottering.<br>
<br>
If you think that all this is a bit too much trouble, try just selling the Vial of Distilled Mana in bazaar. On my server, it sells quite well for 325-350pp giving a 100 pp profit.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps some people out there. It has helped me - I make about 6Kpp each time I do a batch of 20 attempts.<br>
